p: The seed oil fatty acid composition (32-40%) has been reported by various authors to contain mainly, linoleic, linolenic, oleic, palmitoleic, palmitic acids together with arachidonic, eicosadienoic, stearic, and myristic acid [ 15, 16, 19]. A new dienoate and two known monoesters along with novel lipids have been isolated from the unsaponified extract of the seed, namely methylnonadeca-15,17-dienoate, pentyl hexadec-12-enoate, and pentyl pentadec-11-enoate [ 20].
